weather.text: ay : Sunny and warm with a high of 89 degrees. Winds SW 8-12 mph.  Friday : Partly cloudy with a high of 85 degrees. WSW winds 5-10 mph.  Saturday : Partly cloudy with a high of 86 degrees. W winds 5-10 mph.  Sunday : Mostly cloudy turning to partly cloudy in the afternoon with a high of 79 degrees. NE winds 10-15 mph.

notes:
Rickie Fowler,  D.A. Points and Rory McIlroy finished tied at 14-under 274 after 72 holes of the 2012 Wells Fargo Championship, with Fowler making birdie on the first extra hole(No. 18)for his first TOUR win. The playoff was the fifth at the Wells Fargo Championship and second straight on the PGA TOUR(Zurich Classic of New Orleans, Wells Fargo Championship). In 2011, Lucas Glover defeated his former Clemson University teammate Jonathan Byrd to win the Wells Fargo Championship.   
   
   Rickie Fowler, at the age of 23 years, 4 months and 23 days, became the third player to make the Wells Fargo Championship his first PGA TOUR win( Anthony Kim /2008, Rory McIlroy /2010). Fowler is the third-youngest winner of the event, behind McIlroy(20 years, 11 months, 28 days)and Kim(22/10/15).   
   
   Rickie Fowler's opening-round 66 in 2012 the lowest start by a winner of the Wells Fargo Championship.   
   
 With his runner-up finish at the 2012 Wells Fargo Championship, Rory McIlroy regained the top spot in the Official World Golf Ranking. He entered the week needing a two-way tie for seventh or better to move back to No. 1. The runner-up finish was the second of McIlroy's career on the PGA TOUR(2012 World Golf Championships-Accenture Match Play Championship).   
   
   D.A. Points bogeyed his last hole at the 2012 Wells Fargo Championship in his attempt to become the first player to play the final 36 holes without a bogey at the Wells Fargo Championship. He had played the previous 40 holes without a bogey, dating to the par-3 13th hole on Friday.   
   
 Entering the 2012 Wells Fargo Championship, D.A. Points has had minimal success in five starts at the Wells Fargo Championship, with just one made cuts(T63/2010)before his playoff runner-up finish in 2012.   
   
 The 54-hole leader Webb Simpson (4)had gone 220 consecutive holes on TOUR without recording a 3-putt until he did so at the par-4 11th hole in the final round of the 2012 Wells Fargo Championship.   
   
 After 12 consecutive rounds in the 70s to start his career at the Wells Fargo Championship, Lee Westwood closed with rounds of 68-66 in 2012 to snap that streak. His career progress at the event includes a missed cut in 2006, T61 in 2007, T38 in 2010 and T5 in 2012.   
   
 After missing his five cuts at the Wells Fargo Championship, Jonathan Byrd has found his stride at the event, finishing T5(2009), MC(2010), runner-up(2011)and T9(2012).   
   
   Phil Mickelson made his ninth cut in nine starts at the Wells Fargo Championship this week, finishing T26. Mickelson owns six top 10s at Quail Hollow Club(2004-T5, 2005-T7, 2007-T3, 2009-T4, 2010-2, 2011-T9).   
   
   Lucas Glover became the third consecutive defending champion to miss the cut at the Wells Fargo Championship and the fifth overall, joining David Toms (2004), Jim Furyk (2007), Sean O'Hair (2010)and Rory McIlroy (2011).   
   
 The 54-hole leader has won just three of 10 Wells Fargo Championships( David Toms  -2003, Jim Furyk -2006 and Anthony Kim -2008).   
   
   Lucas Glover (2011)remains the only player in the history of the Wells Fargo Championship to post all four rounds in the 60s.   
   
 Nine players have competed in all 10 Wells Fargo Championships through 2012: John Senden (T15), Billy Mayfair (T32), Carl Pettersson (T46), J.J. Henry (T57), Stuart Appleby (MC), Charles Howell III (MC), Jeff Maggert (MC), Rory Sabbatini (MC)and Vijay Singh (MC).   
   
 Four of the eight former Wells Fargo Championship champions in the 2012 field made the cut: Rory McIlroy (P2), David Toms (T15), Sean O'Hair (T15), Jim Furyk (T26).
